The paper introduces a propositional logic for reasoning about expectation, which is a central notion in probability theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), which deals with reasoning and decision-making under uncertainty. The paper also discusses different representations of uncertainty, such as sets of probability measures, belief functions, and possibility measures, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper provides sound and complete axiomatizations for the logic, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of Mathematical Aspects of Computer Science (cs.MA). The paper also deals with the expressiveness of the logic, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Overall, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.DS, and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
